green gecko
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a general name applied to any member of the Naultinus genus of native gecko species each of which has also an individual, usually toponymic, name
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: Environment
Region: [none]
See: Auckland green gecko, Marlborough green gecko,  Nelson green gecko, North Cape green gecko, Northland green gecko, Wellington green gecko, West Coast green gecko
Pronunciation:
Notes: <i>Naultinus</i> genus, as opposed to <i>Hoplodactylus</i>.
