Quote:  NEW ZEALAND is home to two types of geckos, which have generally been described as green (<i>Naultinus</i> genus), and brown (<i>Hoplodctylus</i> genus) geckos. .. Green geckos are relatively easy to distinguish due to their diurnal life-style and their Kermit-green colour schemes, which can include white, yellow or gold stripes, or diamonds on their backs.
